!Topic 26 Dialing Directory (Alt-D)

Phone numbers and related information are stored in the Qmodem Dialing
Directory.   Multiple Dialing Directories may be loaded with up to 200
entries stored in each directory.  QMODEM.FON is the default dialing
directory that is loaded.

Dialing Directory commands allow you to Dial another system, Edit the
current FON book, and attach NOTES to individual entries.

The Phone book is divided into two sections, with each section able to
display two different screens.  The top section will look something like
this:

