The top line tells you which FON file you are viewing and the current page
number.  The next line down tells you how many entries are tagged for dialing
and how many Prefix letters have been defined.


Name  This field is used to name the system.  Length: 27 characters.  It
can be anything you want, but should not be left blank (for sorting reasons).

The Name field can also contain an FKey Hotkey assignment string.  The
example above shows entries 1,2 and 3 with FKeys assigned.  F2 thru F12 can
be assigned to an entry by enclosing the assignment in { } brackets.

Number  This is the phone number to dial.  Length: 19 characters.  You can
put any character in here you want, but make sure it is a subset of your
modem's DIAL command.  In addition, you can use the Prefix modifier
characters A-J to make the number longer than just 19 characters.

COM  This is the serial port parameters to be used.  Baud rate, Data bits,
Parity and Stop bits are shown.
!Page

Script  This is the name of a Script file if one is attached.  Length: 12
Characters.  If you attach a script to an entry, it will get executed
automatically when you dial and get connected.  If the script does not
actually exist, then QuickLearn will create it the first time automatically!


