Password  A convenient place to store system passwords.  Length: 14
characters.  This is more than convenient because there are other built-in
commands that can make use of this field after a connection.  There is a
corresponding Script Language variable called $PASSWORD that is loaded with
the Password in the entry.

LastCall  The date on which you last connected.  This field is
automatically updated every time you call the system and get connected. 
Aborted dial attempts and BUSY's do not update this field.

Total  The number of times you have connected.  Length: 5 digits.  This too
gets updated every time you connect to the system.

P  (for Protocol)  This is the default transfer protocol you want to use on
the system.  If defined, this is placed in the Upload and Download protocol
selection window by default.  If none is defined, you have to select a
protocol for each transfer.

D  (for Duplex)  This is the default Duplex to use when calling the system.
Can be either H for Half Duplex or F for Full Duplex.

Each page of the phone book will display 10 entries, unless you are in 43/50
line mode.  Then you get 20 entries per page (and half as many pages).

