Commands are divided into 5 groups:

ENTRIES  Commands affecting directory entries such as Revise or Delete.

DIAL  Commands which start the dialing or exit the Dialing  Directory.

EDIT  Commands used to edit notes or scripts linked to the current entry.

FON  Commands which manipulate the Directory itself such as Load.

MOVEMENT  Implied Commands/Keys used to navigate through the Directory.  


All changes to the Dialing Directory are saved to the disk immediately.  When
a Revise, Tag with Prefix, Insert, Delete, Sort operation is performed, the
old version of the directory is saved under its current name with the .FBK
extension.

The last major change to the directory can be cancelled with the ^U Undo
command.

